    "shortDescription": "Powered by a 700hp 496ci big-block V8 engine with a Stage 4 4L80E 4-speed automatic transmission. Features",
    "longDescription": "This custom 1960 Chevrolet Corvette convertible was finished in 2022 and is powered by a Mast Motorsports 675hp LS7 engine backed by a TREMEC 6-speed manual transmission with a dual disc clutch and a Be Cool radiator. It sits on a powder-coated Art Morrison chassis and has adjustable ride-height suspension. Stopping power is provided by Wilwood 6-piston brakes on the front and 4-piston on the rear, with 14-inch rotors all around. It also has power rack & pinion steering. The polished stainless-steel exhaust is ceramic-coated and exits through the rear bumper. The fuel system is supplied by a stainless Rock Valley C1 fuel tank. The body was glass bead-stripped and finished in PPG 9000 Tuxedo Black and the inserts vinyl-wrapped in white. The exterior has also been ceramic-coated with Ceramic Pro, which carries a transferable lifetime warranty. The underside was coated in Satin Black, with Euro texture on the underside of the fenders. This Corvette rides on custom billet C1 wheels wrapped in Nitto tires. The red leather interior features fully adjustable seats, a billet leather-wrapped steering wheel and custom stitching throughout. Along with T3 headlights, it also has LED lighting throughout, Dakota Digital gauges, an E-Stopp emergency brake, 2-speed windshield wipers, Wilwood clutch and brake pedals, a Vintage Air system and a retro-looking Wonder Bar Bluetooth stereo with a Rockford Fosgate amplifier and four speakers. The sale includes all of the manuals and an SD card with photos of the entire build.",
